  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: residual-risk-justification gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The turbulence model has known limitations in predicting recirculation-zone shear stress at off-design operating points; this limitation is acknowledged but the package does not document why the associated residual risk is acceptable for the COU.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req",
