    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 4 for Model Risk Level 2. The CFD model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. It is noted that the turbulence model exhibits a known limitation in predicting recirculation-zone shear stress at off-design operating points; this limitation was identified during validation and is acknowledged in the validation results narrative.",
